abstract: National Archives makes public 2,500 documents from Clinton White House, third installment in release of as many as 33,000 documents; some of the most riveting material involves administration’s scramble to contain Monica Lewinsky scandal, which led to the president’s impeachment, and the maneuverings inside White House to prepare for Hillary Rodham Clinton’s political future.
lead_paragraph: The National Archives made public 2,500 documents from the Clinton White House on Friday, the third installment in the release of as many as 33,000 documents.

byline.original: By AMY CHOZICK and DAVID S. JOACHIM

headline.main: Newly Released Clinton-Era Papers Show Damage Control During Scandal
headline.print_headline: Newly Released Clinton-Era Papers Show Damage Control During Scandal
